<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="334" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,968,1607]" pageId="28" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,968,994]" pageId="28" pageNumber="334">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. In the key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Lundbeck, W." box="[437,632,968,994]" pageId="28" pageNumber="334" refId="ref14900" refString="Lundbeck, W. (1922) Diptera Danica Part VI Pipunculidae, Phoridae. Wesley, London, 447 pp." type="book" year="1922">Lundbeck (1922)</bibRefCitation>
for Group VI it runs to couplet 22, but the extensive yellow colouring rules out the species. In the keys to the males of the British species (
<bibRefCitation author="Disney R. H. L." box="[922,1073,1004,1030]" pageId="28" pageNumber="334" pagination="1 - 155" refId="ref14009" refString="Disney R. H. L. (1989) Scuttle Flies-Diptera Phoridae Genus Megaselia. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 10 (8), Royal Entomologicai Society of London, 1 - 155. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631287 X 00115" type="book chapter" year="1989">Disney, 1989</bibRefCitation>
) it runs to couplet 190 lead 1 or couplet 233. The colouring and the hypopygium excludes this species. It fails to run down in keys for the rest of the world’s fauna and subsequent additions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="334" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,968,1607]" pageId="28" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1112,1138]" pageId="28" pageNumber="334">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Frons as 
<figureCitation box="[522,615,1112,1138]" captionStart="FIGURES 213–224" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[265,1312,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-32@29.[265,1322,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 213–224. Megaselia svendi n. sp. male. 213, frons; 214, postpedicel (Fig. 215), palp and proboscis; 216, proboscis from below; 217, left face of thorax; 218, left face of abdomen; 219–220, hypopygium; 221, front tarsus; 222, mid tibia; 223, hind femur; 224, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925259/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="334">Fig. 213</figureCitation>
and devoid of microtrichia. Cheek with 5 bristles and jowl with 2 that are clearly longer and more robust (
<figureCitation box="[515,614,1148,1175]" captionStart="FIGURES 213–224" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[265,1312,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-32@29.[265,1322,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 213–224. Megaselia svendi n. sp. male. 213, frons; 214, postpedicel (Fig. 215), palp and proboscis; 216, proboscis from below; 217, left face of thorax; 218, left face of abdomen; 219–220, hypopygium; 221, front tarsus; 222, mid tibia; 223, hind femur; 224, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925259/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="334">Fig. 216</figureCitation>
). Postpedicels extremely pale and lacking SPS vesicles (
<figureCitation box="[1256,1355,1148,1175]" captionStart="FIGURES 213–224" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[265,1312,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-32@29.[265,1322,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 213–224. Megaselia svendi n. sp. male. 213, frons; 214, postpedicel (Fig. 215), palp and proboscis; 216, proboscis from below; 217, left face of thorax; 218, left face of abdomen; 219–220, hypopygium; 221, front tarsus; 222, mid tibia; 223, hind femur; 224, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925259/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="334">Fig. 215</figureCitation>
). Palps yellow and proboscis as 
<figureCitation box="[435,531,1184,1210]" captionStart="FIGURES 213–224" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[265,1312,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-32@29.[265,1322,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 213–224. Megaselia svendi n. sp. male. 213, frons; 214, postpedicel (Fig. 215), palp and proboscis; 216, proboscis from below; 217, left face of thorax; 218, left face of abdomen; 219–220, hypopygium; 221, front tarsus; 222, mid tibia; 223, hind femur; 224, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925259/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="334">Fig. 214</figureCitation>
and with numerous short spinules below (
<figureCitation box="[1020,1120,1184,1211]" captionStart="FIGURES 213–224" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[265,1312,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-32@29.[265,1322,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 213–224. Megaselia svendi n. sp. male. 213, frons; 214, postpedicel (Fig. 215), palp and proboscis; 216, proboscis from below; 217, left face of thorax; 218, left face of abdomen; 219–220, hypopygium; 221, front tarsus; 222, mid tibia; 223, hind femur; 224, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925259/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="334">Fig. 216</figureCitation>
). Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[1240,1337,1184,1210]" captionStart="FIGURES 213–224" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[265,1312,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-32@29.[265,1322,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 213–224. Megaselia svendi n. sp. male. 213, frons; 214, postpedicel (Fig. 215), palp and proboscis; 216, proboscis from below; 217, left face of thorax; 218, left face of abdomen; 219–220, hypopygium; 221, front tarsus; 222, mid tibia; 223, hind femur; 224, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925259/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="334">Fig. 217</figureCitation>
) yellow, with 3 notopleural bristles and no cleft in front of these, mesopleuron bare, and scutellum with an anterior pair of small hairs and a posterior pair of bristles. Abdomen as 
<figureCitation box="[792,890,1256,1282]" captionStart="FIGURES 213–224" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[265,1312,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-32@29.[265,1322,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 213–224. Megaselia svendi n. sp. male. 213, frons; 214, postpedicel (Fig. 215), palp and proboscis; 216, proboscis from below; 217, left face of thorax; 218, left face of abdomen; 219–220, hypopygium; 221, front tarsus; 222, mid tibia; 223, hind femur; 224, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925259/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="334">Fig. 218</figureCitation>
, with the hypopygium as 
<figureCitation box="[1186,1370,1256,1282]" captionStart="FIGURES 213–224" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[265,1312,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-32@29.[265,1322,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 213–224. Megaselia svendi n. sp. male. 213, frons; 214, postpedicel (Fig. 215), palp and proboscis; 216, proboscis from below; 217, left face of thorax; 218, left face of abdomen; 219–220, hypopygium; 221, front tarsus; 222, mid tibia; 223, hind femur; 224, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925259/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="334">Figs 219 &amp; 220</figureCitation>
. Legs yellow apart from brown tip to the hind femur. Fore tarsus with posterodorsal hair palisade on segments 1–4 (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 213–224" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[265,1312,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-32@29.[265,1322,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 213–224. Megaselia svendi n. sp. male. 213, frons; 214, postpedicel (Fig. 215), palp and proboscis; 216, proboscis from below; 217, left face of thorax; 218, left face of abdomen; 219–220, hypopygium; 221, front tarsus; 222, mid tibia; 223, hind femur; 224, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925259/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="334">Fig. 221</figureCitation>
). Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends about 0.8 times its length (
<figureCitation box="[983,1083,1328,1354]" captionStart="FIGURES 213–224" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[265,1312,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-32@29.[265,1322,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 213–224. Megaselia svendi n. sp. male. 213, frons; 214, postpedicel (Fig. 215), palp and proboscis; 216, proboscis from below; 217, left face of thorax; 218, left face of abdomen; 219–220, hypopygium; 221, front tarsus; 222, mid tibia; 223, hind femur; 224, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925259/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="334">Fig. 222</figureCitation>
). Hind femur as 
<figureCitation box="[1272,1369,1328,1354]" captionStart="FIGURES 213–224" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[265,1312,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-32@29.[265,1322,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 213–224. Megaselia svendi n. sp. male. 213, frons; 214, postpedicel (Fig. 215), palp and proboscis; 216, proboscis from below; 217, left face of thorax; 218, left face of abdomen; 219–220, hypopygium; 221, front tarsus; 222, mid tibia; 223, hind femur; 224, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925259/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="334">Fig. 223</figureCitation>
. Hind tibia with 15–16 differentiated posterodorsal hairs, without anterodorsals, and spinules of apical combs simple. Wings (
<figureCitation box="[239,337,1400,1426]" captionStart="FIGURES 213–224" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[265,1312,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-32@29.[265,1322,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 213–224. Megaselia svendi n. sp. male. 213, frons; 214, postpedicel (Fig. 215), palp and proboscis; 216, proboscis from below; 217, left face of thorax; 218, left face of abdomen; 219–220, hypopygium; 221, front tarsus; 222, mid tibia; 223, hind femur; 224, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925259/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="334">Fig. 224</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[349,392,1400,1426]" captionStart="FIGURE 243" captionStartId="34.[151,250,2016,2040]" captionTargetBox="[215,1372,1121,1992]" captionTargetId="figure-31@34.[215,1372,1121,1992]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 243. Megaselia svendi n.sp., male, right wing, dorsal, detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4925273" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4925273/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="334">243</figureCitation>
) extremely pale and 
<quantity box="[630,731,1400,1427]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.87" pageId="28" pageNumber="334" unit="mm" value="1.87">1.87 mm</quantity>
long. Costal index 0.56. Costal ratios 3.4: 2.8: 1. Costal cilia (of section 3) 
<quantity box="[306,406,1436,1463]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="334" unit="mm" value="0.05">0.05 mm</quantity>
long. Hair at base of vein 3 only 
<quantity box="[777,877,1436,1463]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="334" unit="mm" value="0.01">0.01 mm</quantity>
long. With 3 axillary bristles, the outermost being 
<quantity box="[151,251,1472,1499]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="28" pageNumber="334" unit="mm" value="0.13">0.13 mm</quantity>
long. Sc very pale and reaching or else not quite reaching R1. Haltere almost white.
</paragraph>
